\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
For now:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Klette & Kortum 2004 style model endogenizing knowledge spillovers via workers
 leaving incumbents to start rival startups
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Non-enforcement leads to faster knowledge spillovers, but reduces value
 of knowledge, disincentivizing R&D (c.f.
 Arrow 1962)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Goal: calibrate using LEHD, Crunchbase, LinkedIn data
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Test model by seeing extent to which it can reproduce cross-sectional empirical
 results in the data
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Counterfactual productivity growth and welfare analysis
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Future work: 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Multiple incumbents competing over workers 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Worker human capital accumulation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Endogenous contracting (for now, simply assume that non-competes are used
 in enforcing regimes)
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
